She said the sea would sing to she,
And she believed the silver tree.
She wore the shadow, she wore the rain,
She danced through joy, she danced through pain.

She held the stars, she held the night,
She chased the dark, she chased the light.
She whispered softly, “She will stay,”
While she kept drifting far away.

She saw the snow, she saw the fire,
She climbed above the city spire.
She broke the silence, she broke the spell,
She knew the heaven, she knew the hell.

She was the echo, she was the flame,
She called the wind by secret name.
And she, forever wild and free,
Still sings her song beside the sea.